Search in the Audit Log

Any user with administrator role, is able to perform a search in the audit log and find only actions performed in a time interval, or actions performed by a user, etc.

  • The user selects in the Admin menu the option Audit Log(1-2).

  • In the Audit log screen (1), there is a search section.
  • In the search section the administrator could search by:
    • Object type (2) - by default in the field is selected Any object. The Admin could select one or more object types to search for in the audit log.

The following search criteria could be combined with AND/ OR operands and the user could add in the search query one or more of them (1-2).

  • Action - the Admin could select one or more actions of the existing actions in the system for which he would like to see information about who and when has performed them (the list with actions is the same as the one displayed in the Manage actions per role screen).
  • Event date - the Admin could enter any date interval to search in
  • User - the Admin could select one or more users, for which he would like to see their activities
  • Object - By selecting from a list or creating a nested advance query, the Admin could search for instances that cover specific search criteria. The audit log will display then only information for the selected instances.

  • The user selects search criteria (1) and clicks Search (2).
  • Then the Audit log is restricted to display only information based on the selected search criteria (3-4).
